      }},
      { type: "story", theme: "gold-bg", content: {
        label: "Your Journey", title: "De novice à maître QES",
        text: "You began this course understanding that RCTs measure efficacy. You now understand that <strong>qualitative evidence explains why interventions succeed or fail</strong> in real contexts, with real people, facing real barriers.",
        followup: "Whether you're conducting systematic reviews, developing clinical guidelines, or evaluating programs, you now have the tools to ensure qualitative evidence gets the rigorous treatment it deserves. Go forth and synthesize—the patients whose voices fill qualitative studies are counting on you to make their experiences matter in healthcare decisions."
